<para id="element-77">
<term>4.</term> Moment of inertia, also referred in short as MI, is a scalar quantity. The directional positions (angular positions) of the particles/objects with respect to axis of rotation does not matter. The unit of MI is 
<m:math>
<m:mi> kg </m:mi>
<m:mo> - </m:mo> 
